<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC245C4E294837AFE7A" blockId="5.[174,812,431,458]" box="[174,812,431,458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
<heading id="201B81C76E34FFC245C4E294837AFE7A" box="[174,812,431,458]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="BCEC4D286E34FFC245C4E29482E3FE79" authority="(Dujardin, 1841)" baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[174,693,431,458]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Lepidodermella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis id="4998EAB96E34FFC245C4E29481BFFE7A" bold="true" box="[174,489,431,458]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Lepidodermella squamata</emphasis>
(Dujardin, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E3D72A2E6E34FFC247A9E29482A9FE79" box="[707,767,431,457]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[167,200,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[202,1183,629,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[179,1200,615,1773]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Gastrotrichs of the Karyakiv ravine pond: A — Chaetonotus (Zonochaeta) bisacer, B — Chaetonotus (Primochaetus) heideri, C — Lepidodermella minor minor, D — Lepidodermella squamata, E — Ichthydium maximum, F — Haltidytes festinans. Scale bars 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455652/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, D)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E2D58486FDB3" blockId="5.[174,1232,493,542]" box="[227,1232,493,515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
M a t e r i a l. 
<specimenCount id="6DEAFD226E34FFC24436E2D58181FDB3" box="[348,471,493,515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="generic">4 specimens</specimenCount>
. TL 150–180 µm, al 10–11 µm, pl 37–54 µm, md 7–8 µm, hw 36–39 µm, nw
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33F665206E34FFC245C4E1338399FC29" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="description">
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC245C4E13381CAFDAE" blockId="5.[174,1232,493,542]" box="[174,412,520,542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">29–34 µm, tw 15–18 µm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E17B842EFD49" blockId="5.[174,1233,575,922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
D e s c r i p t i o n. The morphology and the dimensions of the animals collected correspond to the literature data (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC24768E16482EFFDC9" author="Schwank, P." box="[514,697,607,633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="1 - 252" refId="ref3985" refString="Schwank, P. 1990. Gastrotricha. In: Schwoerbel, J., Zwick, P., eds. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa, Band 3. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart, Jena, New York, 1 - 252." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Stocky body. The head is weakly five-lobed. Hypostomium developed. Dorsal head and trunk surface covered by smooth scales with either rounded or squared posterior edge; in the neck region the scales are more rectangular. Ventral interciliary field with transverse scale plates in the pharynx region. Mouth subterminal, pharynx gradually widens towards the pharyngeal intestinal junction.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E03B8122FCCA" blockId="5.[174,1233,575,922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d e c o l o g y. Cosmopolitic species (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC24635E1C48406FCA9" author="Balsamo, M. &amp; d'Hondt, J. L. &amp; Kisielewski, J. &amp; Pierboni, L." box="[863,1104,767,794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="85 - 91" refId="ref3591" refString="Balsamo, M., d'Hondt, J. L., Kisielewski, J., Pierboni, L. 2008. Global diversity of gastrotrichs (Gastrotricha) in fresh waters. Hydrobiologia, 595, 85 - 91." type="journal article" year="2008">Balsamo et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Reported from Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC2443DE02481C1FC89" box="[343,407,799,825]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC244CEE01B81BFFC8A" box="[420,489,800,826]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC2449CE01B8269FC8A" box="[502,575,800,826]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24727E02482C6FC89" box="[589,656,799,825]" name="Israel" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Israel</collectingCountry>
, East Africa, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24645E02483DDFC89" box="[815,907,799,825]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Canada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC246F2E0248384FC89" box="[920,978,799,825]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">USA</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC246B5E0248470FC89" box="[991,1062,799,825]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24159E01B84CDFC8A" box="[1075,1179,800,826]" name="Uruguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC245C4E0048173FCE9" box="[174,293,831,857]" name="Argentina" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC2445EE00481BDFCE9" author="Kanneby T." box="[308,491,831,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="29 - 55" refId="ref3742" refString="Kanneby T. 2011. New species and new records of freshwater Chaetonotida (Gastrotricha) from Sweden. Zootaxa, 3115, 29 - 55." type="journal article" year="2011">Kånneby, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Usually reported from olygo- and mesosaprobic water bodies (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC245DCE064813EFCCA" author="Sladecek, V." box="[182,360,863,890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" refId="ref4033" refString="Sladecek, V. 1976. Indicator value of freshwater Gastrotricha. Acta hydrochim. hydrobiol., 4" type="book" year="1976">Sladeček, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E0448399FC29" blockId="5.[174,1233,575,922]" box="[227,975,895,922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Remarks. This species is reported in 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC247C8E0448354FC29" box="[674,770,895,921]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
